The paper deals with the problem of learning linear prediction models with model misspecification bias, which is a common problem in machine learning. The proposed method involves sample reweighting to reduce collinearity among input variables, which is a technique used in various subfields of computer science such as machine learning (cs.LG), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), statistics (cs.ST), data structures and algorithms (cs.DS), and computer vision (cs.CV). Therefore, these are the most likely sub-categories for this paper.
